org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype

Class OntStateChange<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype.OntStateChange<T>

  • public class OntStateChange<T>
extends Object
    This class is part of a data structure to provide the BCO ontology data (state values of sensors and actuators). The custom data type OntProviderServices expresses the lower-level of the data structure (finest granularity), which includes a concrete state change. Consider in addition the data types OntUnits and OntProviderServices. 1 : N 1 : N OntUnits --- (includes) --- OntProviderServices --- (includes) --- OntStateChange
    Author:
    agatting on 15.09.17.

      • OntStateChange

        public OntStateChange(T type)
               throws org.openbase.jul.exception.InvalidStateException
        Constructor creates a stateChange object, which describes his value parts based on the defined type.
        Parameters:
        type - is the type/subclass of the ontStateChange. It should be one of the classes OntStateChange.Discrete , OntStateChange.Continuous, OntStateChange.AggregatedDiscrete or OntStateChange.AggregatedContinuous.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.InvalidStateException - is thrown in case the input parameter is invalid (null or has wrong type).
